Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186,.proposition: This is a civil action brought by Plaintiff Jessica Martin against Defendant Thomas Reynolds for breach of the covenant of quiet enjoyment under Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186, Section 14.

G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: This court has jurisdiction over this action pursuant to G.L. c. 186, § 14, G.L. c. 231, § 85A, and applicable laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

G.L. c. 231, \u00a7 85A.proposition: This court has jurisdiction over this action pursuant to G.L. c. 186, § 14, G.L. c. 231, § 85A, and applicable laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

G.L. c. 239, \u00a7 8A.proposition: Defendant’s failure to restore hot water violates applicable Massachusetts laws, including but not limited to: G.L. c. 239, § 8A;

G.L. c. 111, \u00a7 127L.proposition: Defendant’s failure to restore hot water violates applicable Massachusetts laws, including but not limited to: G.L. c. 111, § 127L (sanitary conditions in rental housing).
